Email: groch@math.uconn.edu amos@cs.wisc.edu  
Date: September 1996  
Web: 42C30  
Abstract: Based on the method for constructing tight wavelet frames of [RS2], we show that one can construct, for any dilation matrix, and in any spatial dimension, tight wavelet frames generated by compactly supported functions with arbitrarily high smoothness. 
